HEADWORD: Mustaiba
<hw>Mus`ta*i"ba</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A close-grained,
heavy wood of a brownish color, brought from Brazil, and used in
turning, for making the handles of tools, and the like.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>mostahiba</asp>.]</altsp>
<rj><au>MaElrath.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

